Creating images with R

with a little bit of magick

Amanda Hashman

2023-03-07

My meme

My meme was inspired by my husbands reaction when I asked him to cook dinner but left him to decide what to cook.

library(magick)

#top image
sad_monkey <- image_read("./images/sad_monkey.png") %>%
  image_scale(500)

#top text
sad_text <- image_blank(500, 375, color = "#ccc") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "My husband\nwhen I ask him\nto cook dinner", gravity="center", size=60, color="#000", font="sans")

#top row
top_row <- image_append(c(sad_monkey, sad_text))


#bottom image
happy_monkey <- image_read("./images/Happy_Monkey.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(500)

#bottom text
happy_text <- image_blank(500, 500, color = "#ccc") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "My husband\nwhen I tell him\ndinner is ready", gravity="center", size=60, color="#000")

#bottom row
bottom_row <- image_append(c(happy_monkey, happy_text))


#combine it all
meme <- c(top_row, bottom_row) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE) %>%
  image_scale(500)

#save it
image_write(meme, "dinner.png")

My animated gif

After working on the meme I started thinking about what to cook for dinner, and what ingredients I needed for it, so I decided to make a recipe for my husband.

library(magick)

#create frames
lamb <- image_read("./images/lamb.jpg") 
potato <- image_read("./images/potato.jpg")
gravy <- image_read("./images/gravy.jpg")
lamb_shank <- image_read("./images/lamb_shank.jpg") %>%
  image_annotate(text="DINNER", gravity="south", size=75, font="Impact")
plus <- image_read("./images/plus.jpg")
equals <- image_read("./images/equals.jpg")
happy <- image_read("./images/Happy_Monkey.jpg")

#combine them all
frames <- c(lamb, plus, potato, plus, gravy, equals, lamb_shank, happy)

#animate it, shrink it, save it
frames %>%
  image_animate(fps=1) %>%
  image_scale(500) %>%
  image_write("dinner_recipe.gif")
